Some endpoints need to instantiate a configuration instance, set auth method info on it, and then use that configuration when instantiating the api_client.
For each endpoint, can you loop through authmethods, select the first one, set the relevant configuration for it, and then use it?
{{#hasAuthMethods}}
{{authMethods}}
{{#-first}}
{{isBasicBasic}}
config = blah
{{/isBasicBasic}}
{{isBasicBearer}}
config = blah
{{/isBasicBearer}}
{{isHttpSignature}}
config = blah
{{/isHttpSignature}}
{{/-first}}
{{/authMethods}}
with {{{packageName}}}.ApiClient(configuration) as api_client:
{{/hasAuthMethods}}
{{^hasAuthMethods}}
with {{{packageName}}}.ApiClient() as api_client:
{{/hasAuthMethods}}

